HEADWORD: Rocoa
<hw>Ro"coa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>rocou</ets>, <ets>roicou</ets>, Pg. & Braz,
<ets>uruc⟦uacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The orange-colored pulp covering
the seeds of the tropical plant <spn>Bixa Orellana</spn>, from which
annotto is prepared. See <er>Annoto</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

